  "title": "QUANITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p>. Prepare accurate cost estimates for construction projects</p>\n<p>. Analyze and review construction drawings and specifications to determine project requirements</p>\n<p>. Prepare detailed Bills of Quantities (BOQ) and shedules of quantities</p>\n<p>. Prepare and evaluate tender documents and contract documents</p>\n<p>. Review and analyze contractor/sub-contractor quotations</p>\n<p>. Ensure that projects are completed within budget</p>\n<p>. provide advice on cost-effective solutions and value engineering options</p>\n<p>. Negotiate contracts and resolve contractual issues</p>\n<p>. Monitor and control project costs throughout the construction process</p>\n<p>. Prepare cost reports and forcast final project costs</p>\n<p>. Attend site meetings and liaise with clients, contractors and other stakeholders</p>\n<p>. Ensure complice with relevant health and safety regulations</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS : </strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>. </strong>Bachelor's degree in Quantity Surveying or related field</p>\n<p>. At least 3 years of relevant work experience in the construction industry </p>\n<p>. Strong anaytical and problem-solving skills</p>\n<p>. Excellent communications and negotiation skills</p>\n<p>. Proficient in Microsoft Office and relevant Software programs</p>\n<p>. Knowledge of construction contracts and regulations</p>\n<p>. Ability to work well under pressure and meet tight deadlines</p>\n<p>. Willingness to travel to project sites as required</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>If you are a highly motivated individual with a passion for the construction industry and a strong attention to detail, we encoutage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.</p>\n<p><br></p>",
